 Department Overview: Data Science Apps (DSA)
 The Data Science Apps (DSA) team, which sits within the broader Data Intelligence organisation, is a family of multi-talented technologists with backgrounds ranging from Artificial Intelligence to Finance. What connects us all is a shared curiosity for how to drive product strategy with data, a passion for getting the job done, and a healthy disregard for constraints.
 The DSA team, comprising of other data scientists and machine learning engineers, works with other data scientists, engineers, designers, executives, product managers, marketers, customer success, and sales team members across all Cloud businesses to
 discover new opportunities for growth and optimization
 drive data-informed product strategy
 create data product experiences and actionable insights that enable our stakeholders to maximize revenue.
 The team works exclusively with Salesforceâ€™s leaders, providing them with prescriptions to effect the bottom line and solve critical business problems, rather than on external customer-facing products.
 If you were to join us, you would:
 Work closely with a diverse, talented team of data scientists, data and visualisation engineers, analysts, strategists, product managers to create high-visibility data products and decision-making tools for Salesforceâ€™s leaders.
 Work on problems like forecasting important business metrics such as sales and capacity, churn and propensity modelling to retain and grow our customer base, clustering and classification using both structured and unstructured data so we can deliver value and create the most meaningful customer experiences, and so much more!
 Have exposure to and build end-to-end data data science products - develop, maintain and productionalise new and existing models and algorithms that underpin our data science applications.
 Regularly review and update our existing data, models and algorithms to ensure that they remain relevant and to the changes in the broader economy as well as Salesforceâ€™s own business (e.g. acquisitions, introduction of new products, etc.).
 Build ETL pipelines to acquire, prepare and analyse large volumes of internal Salesforce data including data about our Product Utilization, Sales, and Marketing activities to discover patterns, derive actionable product insights and drive development strategies.
 Be part of a team and company that truly cares about your wellbeing and knows how to have fun - both during and after work!
 Examples of attributes we value:
 Advanced knowledge of Machine Learning methods and Statistics
 Good understanding of ML project lifecycle
 2+ years of industry experience and a passion for designing, analyzing and deploying machine learning-based solutions
 Proven ability to find creative solutions to challenging problems using a blend of business context and statistical and ML techniques
 Ability to write good quality, well-documented, scalable code - Python preferred. Experience tools like mlFlow, Airflow, Cron, Docker and Cloud Platforms such as AWS/GCP is a plus
 Solid understanding of data transformations and analytics functions using tools/languages like Pandas, Sklearn, SQL and Spark
 Strong communication skills and ability to tell compelling data stories with audience-appropriate visualizations
 Passion, curiosity, solutions focus and independence
 Perks
 Good work-life balance with excellent wellness benefits for you and your family
 Competitive salaries, generous equity and matched 401k
 Comprehensive health insurance plan including dental and vision
 Flexible PTO and paid volunteering
